0-10000 is my "business" income, my personal income is 40000-50000. Got my first actual credit card in February, but I've had student loans for about 5 years now. Got a Freedom in July and a CSP in September. After my Ink app went pending, I called the automation line the next day and found out I was approved. Make sure you put that your business has been around for at least 2 years when you apply or you'll probably get denied. Other than that, all you can do is pray to the churning gods that your approved when it goes to pending because getting this card is a crapshoot, and DON'T CALL RECON UNLESS YOUR REJECTED.

Just wanted to offer my data point - I applied for a few cards the other day, one of which was the AMEX Green 25k/1k spend. I was automatically denied. I called AMEX to find out why and was told it was because I had a returned payment.
This returned payment was due to my incorrectly setting up a bank account on one of my AMEX cards. I accidentally switched two numbers on my account, so when the auto-payment attempted, it was logged as returned. I called to fix it and they corrected the bank account information and the payment went through fine.
I was told by AMEX that it was automatically denied because of the returned payment. After explaining the situation and notifying them that I paid and was current and that it was just a mix up, she moved my application over to reconsideration and I will hear soon on the outcome. Will keep everyone posted.
Added Note: (this is known to many already but) I was told that they checked my AMEX history first and although I was denied I did not receive a HP. I was told that moving the application over could result in a HP since they check AMEX history before pulling credit information.

We'll get back to you in 30 days" message for both applications. I called the automated status line and it said that both of my apps were under review and that I'd hear back in about two weeks. I called recon immediately (and only mentioned my Sapphire Preferred application) and they wanted to verify my information. The rep got my info and told me that she'd put my application through. I called to check the automated status line again and it said that one of the apps was under review and I would hear back in 7-10 days. The other application still had the two weeks message. FYI, the automated line did not tell me which application corresponded to which card. So I waited about an hour or two and called the status line again. The first app had the 7-10 days message and the second app was approved! I called a Chase representative immediately and asked which card I had just been approved for. It was the Sapphire Reserve for $10k starting limit. I just got a $15k Capital One Venture card a couple weeks ago, but it's not on my credit report and all my other credit is under $5k, so that explains the low limit. I was denied for the Sapphire Preferred because too many recent requests for credit (basically because I was just approved for the Reserve). That was fine with me because I only wanted the Reserve anyway and applied for both for insurance. Also, since I applied within minutes of each other I only got 1 hard pull.
